<h2>What this is</h2>
<p>You will write a <strong>4-page policy brief</strong> on one Chennai-area climate-adaptation challenge for a hypothetical <strong>Greater Chennai Corporation</strong> planning audience. Same GCC audience you wrote for in the <a href="/units/unit-2/assessment-landscape-reading/">Landscape Reading</a> — but now you're operating in policy-brief format, with abstract climate science as the evidence base and concrete adaptation recommendations as the deliverable.</p>
<p>The Brief is defended in a live <strong>Policy Panel</strong> — 4-minute pitch + 3-minute Q&amp;A, with peers playing GCC officials asking cost, feasibility, equity, and science-credibility questions. Higher-stakes defense format than the U2 share-out (longer pitch, longer Q&A, sharper question categories).</p>

